should be_valid_xhtml Rails plugin
==================================

should be_valid_xhtml is a plugin for RSpec that allows you to validate your XHTML templates using the W3C Validator (http://validator.w3.org). It uses RSpec view tests to enable validation of XHTML fragments. In other words, the template without layout.

In spec/views/users/index.html.haml_spec.rb:
    describe 'users/index.html.haml' do
      it do
        assigns[:users] = [mock_model(User, :name => 'Joe')]
        render
        response.body.should be_valid_xhtml
      end
    end




